{"author":{"id":"729f4229091d502775e0e5c4bfc138609955b348584d955f4229a3d76892d2a9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1458142611,"nonce":"seRABJBwmzQoocpJJ02CfLDOBIg=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNDEzMTE5MzQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/679","origin":"github"},"title":"package_python_2_7_10 needs to compile against libcrypto","message":"This is mostly an issue for people using Galaxy in a Docker container, but the hashlib package that comes with `package_python_2_7_10` needs to get linked against libcrypto from openssl. That's not listed as a requirement, so if one installs `package_python_2_7_10` inside a docker container and worker nodes on a cluster don't happen to either have that same version or don't export the version of openssl then a random variety of packages (most notably matplotlib) will be non-functional.","files":null}]}